        configurations - node configurations, keyed by hostname
        ipOwners - network Ip owners (see computeIpNodeOwners(Map, boolean) for reference)
        keepInvalid - whether to keep improperly configured neighbors. If performing configuration checks, you probably want this set to true, otherwise (e.g., computing dataplane) you want this to be false.
        checkReachability - whether to perform dataplane-level checks to ensure that neighbors are reachable and sessions can be established correctly. Note: this is different from keepInvalid=false, which only does filters invalid neighbors at the control-plane level
        tracerouteEngine - an instance of ITracerouteEngine for doing reachability checks.
        dp - (partially) computed dataplane.
        Returns:
        A graph (Network) representing all BGP peerings.
